replies.body:
I actually suggested this in a previous thread of mine. There's already a pretty clear variance of playstyle between all the marksmen, the key gameplay patterns that I've identified are as follow;

**Slayers** - Marksmen who excel at dealing a maximum amount of sustained damage to a single target. This is the most classic definition of a marksman in League. These characters are often characterized by their shorter reach* and on key positioning to catch out priority targets on the enemy team.
Champions - {{champion:133}} {{champion:67}} {{champion:29}} {{champion:119}} {{champion:104}} {{champion:222}} {{champion:429}} {{champion:236}} {{champion:18}} 

**Snipers** - Marksmen usually characterized by their range, safety and ability to make plays from far behind the frontlines. These characters are defined by their ability to use their skills to make the enemy team's life a living hell whether it be by poke pressure or laying down minefields. The utility they bring compliments strategic team compositions rather than their strict damage output. 
Champions - {{champion:51}} {{champion:42}} {{champion:81}} {{champion:202}} {{champion:110}} {{champion:22}}{{champion:96}} 

There is sure to be a bit of overlap where some champions are concerned (Are Kog and Trist snipers or slayers? Kalista deals a lot of damage but has some of the best utility in the game.) but I feel as though these classifications sum up the broad strokes of the Marksmen class.
